Program Description:

	This program implements a superquadric shape in opengl. The program also implements texture mapping on the shape.

How to Build:

Building -

	Once the file is uncompressed simply run the command make in terminal.

Running - 

	./superquadric

Commands -

	j/J - decreases/increases the n bulge factor

	k/K - decreases/increases the m bulge factor

	n/N - decreases/increases the N slice/dice value

	m/M - decreases/increases the M slice/dice value

List of Files:

Makefile - The file to build the program from included source files.

superquadric.c - The source file the implements the superquadric in opengl using glut

matrix.c - Source file includes all required matrix operations.

matrix.h - Header file for matrix.c

README - The README for the program (this file).
